In director Wong Kar Wai's 2000 masterpiece "In The Mood for Love", countless people have been awestricken by the elegant qipao dresses worn by lead actress Maggie Cheung. The maker of those dresses was master tailor Leung Long Kong who today, aged 84, is still working in the city full-time. In this video, we look at how he creates his garments to fully bring out the gracefulness of the women that wear them.